A

AbstractPuzzle - Class in model
Abstract base class for all puzzles like Sudoku, Killer and Str8ts that have a square grid with the constraints that each number has to be in the range from 1 to the number of rows/columns in the grid (see AbstractPuzzle.getGridSize()) and no duplicate values are allowed in a row/column.

isInvalid() - Method in class model.AbstractPuzzle
Returns false if and only if AbstractPuzzle.grid is a square with AbstractPuzzle.gridSize * AbstractPuzzle.gridSize cells, every cell is either AbstractPuzzle.EMPTY_CELL or in the valid range from 1 to AbstractPuzzle.gridSize (both inclusive) and there are no conflicts.
isInvalid() - Method in class model.Killer
Returns false if and only if AbstractPuzzle.grid is a square with AbstractPuzzle.gridSize * AbstractPuzzle.gridSize cells, every cell is either AbstractPuzzle.EMPTY_CELL or in the valid range from 1 to AbstractPuzzle.gridSize (both inclusive), every cell is part of exactly one group, no group is empty, all groups have at most Group#MAX_CELLS cells, the sum of each group is in the valid range from getMinSumForGroupWithNCells() to getMaxSumForGroupWithNCells() (both inclusive), all cells in a group are connected, the total sum of all group sums is the same as Killer.TOTAL_SUM, there are at least Killer.MIN_GROUP_AMOUNT groups and there are no conflicts.
isInvalid() - Method in class model.Str8ts
Returns false if and only if AbstractPuzzle.grid and Str8ts.colors are squares with AbstractPuzzle.gridSize * AbstractPuzzle.gridSize cells, every cell is either AbstractPuzzle.EMPTY_CELL or in the valid range from 1 to AbstractPuzzle.gridSize (both inclusive), every color is not null and there are no conflicts.

Str8ts - Class in model
Concrete final implementation of AbstractPuzzle with the additional constraints of colored cells (white cells are just like every other cell in an AbstractPuzzle, black cells can be empty) and straights (each compartment of white cells must contain a set of consecutive numbers in any order).
